Defining URL:http://hl7.org/fhir/ips/ValueSet/core-problem-list-disorders-uv-ips
Name:nlmcoreproblemlistdisorders
Definition:

The CORE Problem List Subset of SNOMED CT® (Special Subset International Patient Summary)The Clinical Observations Recordings and Encoding (CORE) Problem List Subset is a UMLS CORE Project with the purpose of defining a UMLS subset that is most useful for documenting and encoding clinical information at a summary level. The CORE Problem List Subset includes SNOMED CT concepts and codes that can be used for the problem list, discharge diagnoses, or reason of encounter. SNOMED CORE subset with disorder, finding, event, situation, morphologic abnormalityhttps://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/Snomed/core_subset.html

nlmcoreproblemlistdisorders

The CORE Problem List Subset of SNOMED CT® (Special Subset International Patient Summary)The Clinical Observations Recordings and Encoding (CORE) Problem List Subset is a UMLS CORE Project with the purpose of defining a UMLS subset that is most useful for documenting and encoding clinical information at a summary level. The CORE Problem List Subset includes SNOMED CT concepts and codes that can be used for the problem list, discharge diagnoses, or reason of encounter. SNOMED CORE subset with disorder, finding, event, situation, morphologic abnormalityhttps://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/Snomed/core_subset.html
